TOPICS COVERED (EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA) FOR MACHINE LEARNING)
Introduction to Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

The training session began with an introduction to Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA), an essential phase in the Machine Learning pipeline. Learned that EDA is the process of analyzing and summarizing datasets using statistical methods and visualizations before building Machine Learning models. The trainer explained that EDA helps data scientists understand the characteristics of the dataset, identify patterns, detect anomalies, discover relationships between variables, and make informed decisions during model development.

Discussed why Exploratory Data Analysis is performed after data preprocessing and before model training.

